  "prompt": "What does \"Quora \" mean?",
  "response": "\"Quora\" is the name of a popular question-and-answer website where users can ask questions on a wide range of topics and receive answers from the community. Founded in 2009 by Adam D'Angelo and Charlie Cheever, Quora is designed to be a platform for knowledge sharing, where experts and enthusiasts contribute by providing detailed and informative answers. The site's name is not an acronym; rather, it was chosen because it sounded good and was easy to remember.",
